sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lacI+pL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The PLlac 0-1 promoter is a hybrid regulatory region consisting of the promoter P(L) of phage lambda with the cI binding sites replaced with lacO1. The hybrid design allows for strong promotion that can nevertheless be tightly repressed by LacI, the Lac inhibitor (i.e. repressor) (BBa_C0010) ([LUTZ97]). The activity of the promoter can be regulated over a >600-fold range by IPTG in E.Coli DH5-alpha-Z1 (same paper reference).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
hybrid promoter design to create strong promoter that is, at the same time, highly repressible. note that the upstream operator installed in this hybrid is slightly different than the one in the original source (Lutz and Bujard, 1997). the most upstream operator region is slightly truncated in the represillator version, so that both operators in the hybrid are the same sequence. see references for details. also, the sequence has been truncated after the transcriptional start site.

LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and increase transcription. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Neelaksh Varshney, Grace Kenney, Daniel Shen, Samantha Sutton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2055007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The RBS used is the BBa_B0034, the terminator is the BBA_B0012, the LacI reculated Promoter is the BBa_R0011. The sequence for the FUR Box was obtained from the results of the paper of Quatrini et al. (Citation in our wiki), choosing the Fur box with the best score. The sequence for the FUR protein was obtained from the Acidithiobacillus ferrooxidans genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Inverter with Ferric Uptake Regulator & LacI. Activates gene expression in presence of iron. LacI and FUR proteins are optimized for Acidithiobacillus ferrooxidans.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It does not have a promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Carmen Padilla, Melissa Gonzalez & Melissa Rios

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2055009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence for the FUR Box was obtained from the results of the paper of Quatrini et al. (Citation in our wiki).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Ferric Uptace Regulator Protein codon-optimized for Acidithiobacillus Ferrooxidans, the FUR Protein in presence of iron will block the transcription because it will bind to its FUR Box.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: You will have to add a FUR Box to repress the transcription with this FUR protein in presence of iron.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Carlos Vasquez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2055010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is the FUR Box with the highest score in the work of: Quatrini, R., Lefimil, C., Veloso, F. A., Pedroso, I., Holmes, D. S., & Jedlicki, E. (2007). Bioinformatic prediction and experimental verification of Fur-regulated genes in the extreme acidophile Acidithiobacillus ferrooxidans. Nucleic Acids Research, 35(7), 2153???2166. http://doi.org/10.1093/nar/gkm068
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a FUR Box with high affinity to BBa_K2055009. In presence of iron, it will block the downstream transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It needs iron to block transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Carlos Vasquez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2055012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from the Acidithiobacillus Ferrooxidans genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Tetrathionate Hydrolase, TetH codon-optimized for Acidithiobacillus Ferrooxidans. It codes for the enzyme that converts tetrathionate to thiosulfate and sulfur.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is an extracellular matrix enzyme for A. Ferrooxidans.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Carlos Vasquez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from luxICDABEG operon terminator of Vibrio fischeri <genbank>AF170104</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Bidirectional transcriptional terminator consisting of a 22 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In the naturally-occuring sequence there is a mismatch in the stem of the stem loop. This can be corrected via an A->G mutation (at position 40 -- sequence coordinate/not MFOLD coordinate). The above sequence does not reflect this mutation (but the MFOLD image does). This terminator's location cannot be found using some inverted repeat detectors like PALINDROME because it is too short and contains a mismatch. This one was found with the help of Tom Knight. It lies between two coding regions that point towards eachother.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
